{
  "id": "burbank-notes-lions-n",
  "slug": "lions",
  "type": "annotation",
  "title": "On the Rialto",
  "sourceFile": "Burbank_notes/Lions_N.htm",
  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table bordercolor=\"#000080\">\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>lion's\n        wings</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>The original draft read lion's <em>mane</em>,\n        and wings was suggested by Pound. The winged lion is the\n        symbol of St. Mark and hence of Venice, of whom St. Mark\n        was the patron saint. The idea is that Venice has been\n        dressed up and domesticised, as for a cat-show, an image\n        Eliot may have gotten from Théophile Gautier (<em>Italia</em>).</font></p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>Venice indirectly</td>\n<td><a href=\"Stones_JR.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Venice misrepresented</td>\n<td><a href=\"Stonesi_JR.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Romance vs Realism</td>\n<td><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>structural analysis</td>\n<td><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"IMG_Rialto1988.htm\"><img src=\"../images/pic.gif\"/></a><a href=\"IMG_StMark.htm\">\n                St. Mark &amp; Lion, Venice 1988</a></td>\n<td> </td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\"</font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "lion's wings The original draft read lion's mane , and wings was suggested by Pound. The winged lion is the symbol of St. Mark and hence of Venice, of whom St. Mark was the patron saint. The idea is that Venice has been dressed up and domesticised, as for a cat-show, an image Eliot may have gotten from Théophile Gautier ( Italia ). reference topics Venice indirectly Venice misrepresented Romance vs Realism structural analysis St. Mark & Lion, Venice 1988 back to \"Burbank\"",
